      "content": "hey im seeing some weirdness in our ec2 instances. getting \"Connection reset by peer\" errors in the logs every few hours but it's totally intermittent. here is a snippet of the cloudwatch log:\n\n2023-10-24T14:22:01Z i-04f928db32 [ERROR] Connection reset by peer (ConnectionException)\n2023-10-24T15:45:12Z i-04f928db32 [ERROR] Connection reset by peer (ConnectionException)\n\ncould this be an issue with the security group settings or maybe an idle timeout?",
